=head2 AutomaticBackupRetentionDays => Int




=head2 DailyAutomaticBackupStartTime => Str




=head2 DeploymentType => Str

Specifies the FSx for ONTAP file system deployment type in use in the
file system.

=over

=item *

C<MULTI_AZ_1> - A high availability file system configured for Multi-AZ
redundancy to tolerate temporary Availability Zone (AZ) unavailability.
This is a first-generation FSx for ONTAP file system.

=item *

C<MULTI_AZ_2> - A high availability file system configured for Multi-AZ
redundancy to tolerate temporary AZ unavailability. This is a
second-generation FSx for ONTAP file system.

=item *

C<SINGLE_AZ_1> - A file system configured for Single-AZ redundancy.
This is a first-generation FSx for ONTAP file system.

=item *

C<SINGLE_AZ_2> - A file system configured with multiple
high-availability (HA) pairs for Single-AZ redundancy. This is a
second-generation FSx for ONTAP file system.

=back

For information about the use cases for Multi-AZ and Single-AZ
deployments, refer to Choosing Multi-AZ or Single-AZ file system
deployment
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/fsx/latest/ONTAPGuide/high-availability-multiAZ.html).


=head2 DiskIopsConfiguration => L<Paws::FSX::DiskIopsConfiguration>

The SSD IOPS configuration for the ONTAP file system, specifying the
number of provisioned IOPS and the provision mode.


=head2 EndpointIpAddressRange => Str

(Multi-AZ only) Specifies the IP address range in which the endpoints
to access your file system will be created. By default in the Amazon
FSx API, Amazon FSx selects an unused IP address range for you from the
198.19.* range. By default in the Amazon FSx console, Amazon FSx
chooses the last 64 IP addresses from the VPCE<rsquo>s primary CIDR
range to use as the endpoint IP address range for the file system. You
can have overlapping endpoint IP addresses for file systems deployed in
the same VPC/route tables.


=head2 Endpoints => L<Paws::FSX::FileSystemEndpoints>

The C<Management> and C<Intercluster> endpoints that are used to access
data or to manage the file system using the NetApp ONTAP CLI, REST API,
or NetApp SnapMirror.


=head2 FsxAdminPassword => Str

You can use the C<fsxadmin> user account to access the NetApp ONTAP CLI
and REST API. The password value is always redacted in the response.


=head2 HAPairs => Int

Specifies how many high-availability (HA) file server pairs the file
system will have. The default value is 1. The value of this property
affects the values of C<StorageCapacity>, C<Iops>, and
C<ThroughputCapacity>. For more information, see High-availability (HA)
pairs (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/fsx/latest/ONTAPGuide/HA-pairs.html)
in the FSx for ONTAP user guide.

Amazon FSx responds with an HTTP status code 400 (Bad Request) for the
following conditions:

=over

=item *

The value of C<HAPairs> is less than 1 or greater than 12.

=item *

The value of C<HAPairs> is greater than 1 and the value of
C<DeploymentType> is C<SINGLE_AZ_1>, C<MULTI_AZ_1>, or C<MULTI_AZ_2>.

=back



=head2 PreferredSubnetId => Str




=head2 RouteTableIds => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

(Multi-AZ only) The VPC route tables in which your file system's
