=head2 ThroughputCapacity => Int




=head2 ThroughputCapacityPerHAPair => Int

Use to choose the throughput capacity per HA pair. When the value of
C<HAPairs> is equal to 1, the value of C<ThroughputCapacityPerHAPair>
is the total throughput for the file system.

This field and C<ThroughputCapacity> cannot be defined in the same API
call, but one is required.

This field and C<ThroughputCapacity> are the same for file systems with
one HA pair.

=over

=item *

For C<SINGLE_AZ_1> and C<MULTI_AZ_1> file systems, valid values are
128, 256, 512, 1024, 2048, or 4096 MBps.

=item *

For C<SINGLE_AZ_2>, valid values are 1536, 3072, or 6144 MBps.

=item *

For C<MULTI_AZ_2>, valid values are 384, 768, 1536, 3072, or 6144 MBps.

=back

Amazon FSx responds with an HTTP status code 400 (Bad Request) for the
following conditions:

=over

=item *

The value of C<ThroughputCapacity> and C<ThroughputCapacityPerHAPair>
are not the same value.

=item *

The value of deployment type is C<SINGLE_AZ_2> and
C<ThroughputCapacity> / C<ThroughputCapacityPerHAPair> is not a valid
HA pair (a value between 1 and 12).

=item *

The value of C<ThroughputCapacityPerHAPair> is not a valid value.

=back



